== Sweet Potato Chips ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over half the @chermoula spice mix{1}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Harissa Beef ==

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a spoon to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Stir the garlic, @harissa paste{50%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and remaining @chermoula spice mix{1} into the beef, then cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat, then cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} to keep warm.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Cucumber Yoghurt ==

Pick the @mint{1/2}(leaves picked from stalks and roughly chopped) from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the cucumber with the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and half the mint. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

== Assembly ==

When the chips have a few mins left, pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven until warm and starting to turn golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

When everything is ready, lay the flatbreads on your plates and top with the harissa beef (reheat first if needed).

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g} over the top, then scatter with the remaining mint.

Serve your loaded flatbreads with the sweet potato chips and cucumber yoghurt alongside.

Enjoy!